  "analysis_notes": {
    "electoral_vote_split": "Maine and Nebraska are the only states that split electoral votes by congressional district. ME-1 (coastal/southern, includes Portland) reliably votes Democratic; ME-2 (rural/northern) reliably votes Republican. This has happened in 2016, 2020, and 2024.",
    "county_flips": "Kennebec County flipped from Democratic (2020) to Republican (2024) — the only county flip in Maine. Biden won it by ~3 points in 2020; Trump won it by ~2.8 points in 2024.",
    "turnout": "74.2% statewide per Wikipedia. Individual county turnout of registered voters ranges from 77-80% in most counties. Note: turnout percentages may differ when using Voting Eligible Population (VEP) vs registered voters as denominator.",
    "party_registration": "Maine has semi-closed primaries but open general elections. Unenrolled (independent) voters are the largest or second-largest bloc in most counties. Green Party is a recognized party in Maine with significant registration. 'No Labels' gained official party status in 2024.",
    "data_caveats": "Voter registration figures are from 11/5/2024 (election day) Maine SOS data. County-level presidential vote totals come from the Wikipedia county results table, which sums to slightly different totals than the certified statewide results in the infobox (county table: Harris 430,342 vs infobox: 435,652). Census data is from 2023 ACS 5-year estimates."
  }
